\\ DEFINING MAIN() IN A PROGRAMMER-DEFINED CLASS //

public class BasicCar { 
  private int milesDriven // Total miles driven by a car

public BasicCar() { // Constructor assigns intial values to instance variables 
  milesDriven = 0; 

public void drive(int tripMiles) { 
  milesDriven - milesDriven + tripMiles;

public int checkOdometer() {
  return milesDriven;
}

public static void main(String [] args) { // Main() creates objects of type BasicCar 
  BasicCar redCorvette = new BasicCar(); // calls methods to operate on the objects 
  BasicCar forMustang = new BasicCar();

  redCorvette.drive(100);
  fordMustang.drive(75);
  forMustang.drive(300);
  fordMustang.drive(50);

UNIT TESTING (CLASSES) //

TESTBENCHES **

Unit testing - create and run a testbench for a speicifc item (or "unit") like a method or a class. 

Regression testing means to reset an item like a class anytime that item is changed; if previously-passed test cases fail, the item has "regressed".




